ame occurs occasionally in England as early as  1300 , and more frequently from the early 16th century, when there was a surge of admiration for, and imitation of, Italian Renaissance culture."]},{"name":"Frances","meanings":["Feminine form of   Francis .  In the 16th century the two spellings were used indiscriminately for both sexes, the distinction in spelling not being established until the 17th century."]}]},{"name":"Berthold","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["<i>berht</i> ‘bright’ + <i>hold</i> ‘splendid’; alteration of earlier <i>Bertwald</i>, from <i>berht</i> + <i>wald</i> ‘rule, power’."],"variants":[{"name":"Barthold","meanings":["form of   Berthold ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Mrs Frau Berthold Stammler was born in 1226, in Ulm, Ulm, Württemberg, Germany. She married Berthold Stammler in 1244, in Ulm, Ulm, Württemberg, Germany. They were the parents of at least 1 son."},"et":{"1226–":"1226–Surnud","1224–1258":"1224–1258","1240–1296":"1240–1296","1226–Female":"1226–Surnud","1226":"1226","1258":"1258","1224":"1224","von um 1240 zu 1245":"umbes 1240 kuni 1245","1244":"1244","1296":"1296","1240":"1240","Ulm, Stadtkreis, Baden-Württemberg, Germany":"Ulm, Oberamt Ulm, Württemberg, Saksamaa"},"fi":{"1226–":"1226–Kuollut","1224–1258":"1224–1258","1240–1296":"1240–1296","1226–Female":"1226–Kuollut","1226":"1226","1258":"1258","1224":"1224","von um 1240 zu 1245":"vuodesta noin 1240 vuoteen 1245","1244":"1244","1296":"1296","1240":"1240","Ulm, Stadtkreis, Baden-Württemberg, Germany":"Ulm, Oberamt Ulm, Württemberg, Saksa"},"fr":{"1226–":"1226–Décédée","1224–1258":"1224–1258","1240–1296":"1240–1296","1226–Female":"1226–Décédée","1226":"1226","1258":"1258","1224":"1224","von um 1240 zu 1245":"du environ 1240 au 1245","1244":"1244","1296":"1296","1240":"1240","Ulm, Stadtkreis, Baden-Württemberg, Germany":"Ulm, Oberamt Ulm, Württemberg, Allemagne","lifeSummary":"Mrs Frau Berthold Stammler 